entries.meaning: (printing) A thin frame in a printing press that holds the sheet of paper in position and acts as a mask.
examples: And while the Tympan is coming , he slips his Left Hand Fingers from under the Frisket to the hither outer corner of it , as well to keep the Sheet close to the Tympan in its position , as to avoid the jobbing of the lower side of the Frisket against the small square shoulder
